Basic Sanitizer (secureRef.sanitize(input: string))
Simple XSS strip (regex-based, for quick use).


5.2 Extended Features (v1.1.0 - Modular Exports)
Keep core small; these are tree-shakable.

Secure Cookies (secureRef.cookie(options))
httpOnly: true, secure: true, sameSite: 'Strict', maxAge: 3600

CSP Nonce Generator (secureRef.nonce())
Crypto-random nonce + browser usage example.

Rate Limiter (secureRef.rateLimit(config))
In-memory token bucket (configurable window/max).

JWT Helpers (secureRef.jwt)
sign(payload, secret), verify(token, secret) with OWASP JWT best practices enforced.

Security Logger (secureRef.log(event, data))
Console + Sentry-ready.

SRI Hash (secureRef.sri(url)): Subresource Integrity for CDNs.
Package Scanner (secureRef.scan()): Runs npm audit + supply chain checks.

Feature Prioritization:

Must-Have: Core middleware + reference.
Should-Have: Cookies, nonce, rate limit.
Could-Have: JWT, logger, SRI.


6. Technical Requirements
Architecture

Entry Point: src/index.ts (ESM + CJS dual).
Structure:textsecure-ref/
├── src/
│   ├── index.ts          # Main export
│   ├── reference.ts      # Static JSON data
│   ├── middleware.ts
│   ├── helpers/          # cookies.ts, nonce.ts, etc.
│   └── types.ts
├── dist/                 # Built
├── examples/             # Express, Fastify, etc.
├── tests/                # Vitest
└── reference.json        # Source of truth for refs

Tech Stack

Runtime: Node.js 18+ (LTS).
Build: tsc + esbuild (for minification).
Types: Full TypeScript + JSDoc.
Testing: Vitest (unit + e2e).
Linting: ESLint + Prettier.

API Signature
TypeScriptimport secureRef, { cookie, nonce, rateLimit } from 'secure-ref';

app.use(secureRef({ /* opts */ }));

const ref = secureRef.reference();
const token = secureRef.jwt.sign({ user: 'shaik' }, process.env.SECRET);

7. Non-Functional Requirements

Size: Core <3KB gzipped; full <5KB.
Performance: <1ms/request overhead.
Security:
Zero runtime deps.
Enable npm provenance.
npm audit clean.
Follow OWASP Node.js Cheat Sheet.

Browser Support: Reference works in browsers (via secure-ref/browser).
License: MIT.
Docs: README.md with badges, examples, migration guide.


8. Dependencies & Constraints

Zero Runtime Deps: Use only crypto, http, url.
Dev Deps: typescript, vitest, @types/node.
No External APIs: All data embedded.
Constraints: No breaking changes in v1.x.


9. Security & Compliance

Package Security:
2FA on npm/GitHub.
Signed commits.
SECURITY.md with reporting.

App Security:
Aligns with OWASP Top 10:2025 (A02, A03).
Supply chain: Pin all dev deps.

Compliance: GDPR-ready (no tracking), SOC2-friendly.

